message.content: cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.CYBER, cs.SI, cs.ET - The paper discusses the design of human-machine interfaces for industrial automatic machines and robotic cells, which involves aspects of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), robotics (cs.RO), cybersecurity (cs.CYBER), and systems and control (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper emphasizes the need for inclusive design, which relates to ethical and social implications (cs.ET) of technology.
